<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - INSTALL - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Before installing the auxiliary drive gear, the mainshaft must be completely installed.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the splined washer on the mainshaft, against the reverse gear retaining snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l5">Figure 215</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017l5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017l5" filename="../figg13/G13017L5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 215. Splined Washer On Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the auxiliary drive gear assembly on the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l6">Figure 216</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017l6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017l6" filename="../figg13/G13017L6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 216. Auxiliary Drive Gear Assembly On Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-end driver and maul to seat the auxiliary drive gear bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the retainer ring bolt holes with the tapped holes (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l6">Figure 216</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l6">Figure 216</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts, and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m) of
                torque.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the splined washer inside the auxiliary drive gear assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l6">Figure 216</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the auxiliary drive gear retaining snap ring in the mainshaft snap ring groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l7">Figure 217</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017l7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017l7" filename="../figg13/G13017L7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 217. Auxiliary Drive Gear Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
